-- Pakistani stocks end lower; rupee steady, o/n rates fall
-- 
-- Fri Oct 17, 2014 09:27AM EDT
-- None



KARACHI, Oct 17 (Reuters) - Pakistani stocks ended lower on Friday, with the benchmark 100-share index of the Karachi Stock Exchange <.KSE> falling 0.33 percent, or 99.35 points, to 29,883.10.

The market remained range-bound as investors continued trimming their portfolios. Oil stocks saw some relief after international oil prices recovered, said Samar Iqbal, a dealer at Topline Securities. Oil and Gas Development Co Ltd <OGDC.KA> rose 0.04 percent to 235.24 rupees while Dewan Farooq Motors Ltd <DEFM.KA> closed down 2.72 percent at 10.00 rupees. The rupee <PKR=> ended almost steady 102.84/102.89 against the dollar, compared with Thursday's close of 102.82/102.88.